 	<li id="block-7cd86fda-6232-4f77-9612-d21cbd66e7bb" class="block-editor-block-list__block wp-block wp-block-list-item block-editor-block-list__layout" role="document" aria-label="Block: List item" data-block="7cd86fda-6232-4f77-9612-d21cbd66e7bb" data-type="core/list-item" data-title="List item">
<div class="block-editor-rich-text__editable rich-text" role="textbox" aria-label="List text" data-wp-block-attribute-key="content">Expanded to include what you've learned through research about technologies of creation and distribution/access/discovery.</div></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="block-fb0a7172-7a14-4ffc-9ab8-9179b05d8a2c" class="block-editor-rich-text__editable block-editor-block-list__block wp-block wp-block-heading rich-text is-hovered" role="document" aria-label="Block: Heading" data-block="fb0a7172-7a14-4ffc-9ab8-9179b05d8a2c" data-type="core/heading" data-title="Heading" data-wp-block-attribute-key="content">Another option! I'm open to new ideas.</h3>
<h1>Final Exam</h1>
Describe a discovery technology that will best support a community of artists that you belong to or value. That might be comic book illustrators, as-yet-undiscovered hip-hop artists, romance novelists, or something else. Think specifically about ways you can help connect fans with the work these artists are producing.

Now describe a discovery technology that will best support a community of consumers/fans that you belong to or value.

Is there any difference between the design of two technologies? If so, why?]]></content:encoded>
