		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This page will be updated as new student work is submitted for inclusion. If you'd like your student work to be included in a future edition, please reach out!
<h1>Modernisms, Spring 2024</h1>
The examples below are not responding to the exact assignment prompts in this book. The assignment prompts students are responding to are gathered on the <a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/about/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"About This Course"</a> page.
<h2>Narration</h2>
<p class="post-title"><a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/revised-yoton-yo-and-interest-by-alienation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">“Yötön Yö” and Interest by Alienation</a> by Liz Radko</p>
<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/revised-finding-my-happy-place-in-emily-henrys-books/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Finding My Happy Place in Emily Henry's Books"</a> by Gina M. Beattie
<h2>Storyworld</h2>
<p class="post-title"><a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/revised-exploring-the-absurd-world-and-legacy-of-moon-remix-rpg-adventure/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Exploring the Absurd World and Legacy of moon: Remix RPG Adventure"</a> by Tristan Onofre</p>
<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/lord-arthur-saviles-crime/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Lord Arthur Savile's Crime"</a> by Monica Dobson
<h2>Character</h2>
<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/28/revised-what-makes-a-character/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"What Makes a Character"</a> by Josh Bird
<p class="post-title"><a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/revised-drawing-a-line-between-the-sympathetic-and-the-insufferable/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Drawing a Line Between the Sympathetic and the Insufferable"</a> by Liz Radko</p>

<h2>Plot</h2>
<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/modernisms/2024/04/29/revised-exploring-emotion-and-sexuality-in-miss-sophias-diary/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Exploring Emotion and Sexuality in 'Miss Sophia's Diary'"</a> by Liz Radko

&nbsp;
<h1>Algorithms and the Arts</h1>
<h2>Getting Started</h2>
"<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/algorithms-and-arts/2024/09/15/watchmen-a-comic-like-no-other/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watchmen: A Comic Like No Other</a>" by Benjamin George

"<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/algorithms-and-arts/2024/09/11/ints2301-01-lizondro-temp-title-tlou/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">It's About the Little Things</a>" by Benjamin Lizondro

"<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/algorithms-and-arts/2024/09/24/the-greatest-story-ever-told/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Greatest Story Ever Told</a>" by Isaac
<h2>Film</h2>
<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/algorithms-and-arts/2024/10/02/are-we-really-special/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Are We Really 'Special'"?</a> by Isaac

<a href="https://unewhavendh.org/algorithms-and-arts/2024/09/25/temp-title-dbz-fr-lizondro/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Connection of Fusion Reborn</a> by Benjamin Lizondro
